Dale Amon wrote:
> However, if reading the serial number resets the modified
> state, what happens if two browsers happen to be sitting
> on the same section of the directory hierarchy at the
> same time? What if they are on slow NFS links?
Are you talking about the serial number scheme in general, or Alan's
poll() problem?
W.r.t. poll(), a good point.  One bit of state needs to be maintained
per file descriptor.  I guess that reduces to the same "since the last
poll" problem.
I don't think slow NFS links is an issue.
